task.summary: added / improved lyrics grouping and sorting algorithm. Any solo's or instrumental parts which include guitar chords are now shown in the UI as well :) and changed some tabs files
changed search lyrics bit so that if no lyrics are found, this is stored in a String[] so that the java backend can survive this.
Some bug fixes concerning accents on titles.
Changed list_files.py so that cmdline doesn't quit at end
changed remote server address to home address external ip

on ultimate guitar tab. A break could have lyrics with chords (this was handlede correctly before) or just chords (this wouldn't show up). Now it is handled correctly. If the break has just chords, it will be handled like a solo. If it does have lyrics, it will be handled as lyrics.
updated version in the script as well :)
quick fix to replace "'" with "" in searching genius lyrics
quick fix to replace "'" with "" in searching genius lyrics
fix in grouping on keywords algorithm to not group all text in intro if that is the only keyword given
fix in grouping on keywords algorithm to not group all text in intro if that is the only keyword given, now with updated version variable
added functionality to re-sync a song while it is playing. Simply press space to enter sync-mode at the point it is. Could be usefull if part of the song is correctly synced but part of it is not.
removed searching tabs on just song title (mostly finds another song anyway)
updated the searching for lyrics algorithm so that a library is first used on genius.com and only than azlyrics is used. Most songs are now found better.
